## I. THE CORE PARADOX OF LIQUIDITY ENCLOSURE
This thesis presents the structural framework analyzing how high-frequency asset pricing models operating on the ticker SPY utilize short-dated derivatives to manage index volatility. 

Autonomous trading networks utilize natural language processing (NLP) to ingest real-time news streams, translating narrative developments into immediate delta-hedging adjustments that dictate the daily trading boundaries.

